snippet.title: "Corporate Retreat" Horror-Dark Comedy | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Climbing the corporate ladder is not for the weak. Do you have what it takes to survive?

ABOUT CORPORATE RETREAT
Hailed “A bloody white-knuckle ride that redefines the modern horror genre” by Tony Toscano of screenchatter.com, and “A bloody good time” by Jeff K. Howard, Vegas Film Critic, the film is directed by Aaron Fisher (“Inside The Rain”) and co-written by Kerri Lee Romeo and Aaron Fisher.

Starring Alan Ruck, Odeya Rush, Ashton Sanders, Rosanna Arquette, Sasha Lane, Zion Moreno, Tyler Alvarez, Benjamin Norris, “Corporate Retreat” is a horror-dark comedy feature film following an ensemble of ambitious young executives whose luxury team-building getaway descends into a bloody fight for survival.  The film blends the dread of gory survival horror with dark laughs and shocking twists.

Passage Pictures presents an Uri Singer Production of an Aaron Fisher Film.

What is Roblox? ROBLOX is an online virtual playground and workshop, where kids of all ages can safely interact, create, have fun, and learn. It’s unique in that practically everything on ROBLOX is designed and constructed by members of the community. ROBLOX is designed for 13 to 18 year olds, but it is open to people of all ages. Each player starts by choosing an avatar and giving it an identity. They can then explore ROBLOX — interacting with others by chatting, playing games, or collaborating on creative projects. Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything — be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer “Capture the Flag” game or some other, yet-to-be-dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (“Robux”). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.

By combining various effects, sound design, and AI technologies, I’ve crafted a cinematic experience that reimagines familiar worlds in bold and imaginative ways. This trailer is not official and is intended to entertain, inspire, and engage with the YouTube community. Thank you for your support — now let’s dive into a world shaped by creativity and craft. 🎬✨

— In this concept trailer for Avengers: Doomsday, the story follows a fragile offshoot of the timeline created during the events of Avengers: Endgame, where Thanos survives not as a conqueror but as an exile who has deliberately abandoned power, ideology, and destiny in search of quiet absolution. Believing the universe has moved on without him, Thanos comes to understand that time itself does not forget, and that unresolved fractures from the Time Heist continue to destabilize reality across the multiverse. As these fractures resurface, his very existence becomes a threat to the fragile world he now inhabits, forcing him to confront the truth that retreat does not absolve responsibility. Torn between remaining a silent witness to collapse or reclaiming agency over the consequences he helped create, Thanos is pushed toward a final reckoning that reframes his role not as a tyrant chasing balance, but as a singular force capable of shaping what survives when inevitability returns.
